      "writtenOn": "2021-06-15T20:37:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, that would line up with how most C++ FPs are written today - the nullptr input gets added. Doing it unconditionally like that would at least make the one-off logic for child indexing non-conditional, though it means burning the one pre-allocated slot in fChildProcessors all the time. Of course, the number of shader-like FPs that have exactly one child is probably pretty small, so maybe that\u0027s fine.",
      "parentUuid": "90f70a67_cb515d79",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 99,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 101,
        "endChar": 5
      },
